Education CS Fred Matiang&rsquo;i and senior officers from the ministry of Education are to visit more than 400 examination centres for KCPE and KCSE.Yesterday, Matiang&rsquo;i witnessed the collection of KCPE papers at subcounty headquarters in Nairobi. He began with Dagoretti in Kawangware at 5am and later toured Westlands, Starehe and Kamukunji.The CS visited Nairobi Primary School, where he witnessed opening of the examinations packets. The school has 60 candidates. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m satisfied with the way the exercise is going on,&rdquo; Matiang&rsquo;i said. He said the supervision will continue. KCSE exams begin on Monday next week until the end of November.&ldquo;The visits will provide a sample from which to assess the efficiency and effectiveness of the measures the government has put in place to safeguard the integrity and credibility of this year&rsquo;s examinations going forward,&rdquo; he said. The visits also target collection and distribution centres. The spot checks complement head teachers, principals and supervisors&rsquo; work.